The main objective of this project is to enhance sustainability, financial viability and social impact of Civil Society Organisations (CSOs) and non-state actors supporting social needs-driven development. This project will:
•	strengthen skills and knowledge on social entrepreneurship of (CSOs) and social enterprises, promote partnerships/networking between CSOs and social enterprises working in the same social domain  and raise public awareness on social entrepreneurship;
•	strengthen institutional, policy and regulatory framework related to social entrepreneurship in Türkiye.
For this purpose, various capacity building and awareness raising activities, such as, organization of trainings, workshops, networking events and study visits, provision of consultancy services and development of tools will be realised in line with technical studies, plans, policy papers and reports that are also expected to be prepared by the contractor under this contract.

The review will also elaborate on the implications the Decommissioning Plan has in terms of the internal organization that JRC needs to set up to manage the decommissioning of HFR effectively and efficiently.

The scope of this lot includes the supply and, where required, delivery of general building materials and associated services for planned works, new build, investment and repairs and maintenance works. This would include, but not be limited to products including timber, boards, roofing, insulation, brick and block, paving, landscape materials and drainage, cement and plaster, carpentry and woodwork, tool purchase (all hardware), kitchens and bathrooms, alarms (smoke/heat/carbon monoxide); ironmongery and any other general building materials.

The scope of this lot includes the supply and, where required, delivery of electrical products and associated services for planned, new build, responsive repair and compliance works. This would include, but not be limited to; cable and wiring, lighting fixtures and fittings, fire and heat detection alarms, circuit protection, ventilation products, electrical accessories, adherence to WEEE regulations

The scope of this lot provides the opportunity to access the supply and delivery of plumbing and heating products and associated services for; new build, planned and responsive repair works — Including, but not limited to, commercial and domestic heating and plumbing systems and spares, communal heating systems, brassware, showering, consumables and associated accessories, Also access to the supply and delivery of gas heating spares and associated services for domestic boilers and fires.

The scope of this lot provides opportunity to access a bespoke designed supply and service for both planned and reactive works and maintenance. This would include the supply of a broad range of products, including, but not limited to; plumbing and heating products; building materials; electrical items; gas spares; tool purchase; any other associated services and requirements within the scope of the framework (across all lots). The location of the store may be on the Members own premises, a dedicated facility or via a dedicated section of the suppliers trade store.

The scope of this lot includes the provision of local bespoke supply and service requirements for both planned and reactive maintenance through Independent merchants who are Members of an awarded national association or body – to include the supply of a broad range of products, including, but not limited to, plumbing and heating products, building materials, electrical; giving members the opportunity to reinvest their funds in local businesses and independent traders where desired. This can be structured by geographic region or on national basis dependent upon the specific requirement.

The scope of this lot provides the supply and, where required, delivery of all grades of roofing materials & associated services required to increase the lifespan of resident homes for planned, new build and maintenance works as well as non-residential properties. Products should include but are not limited to; slates, felts, sheets, tiles, accessories and fixings – flat and pitched roofs.

Provides the supply and delivery of cabinets, units and associated shelving, doors and drawers of all materials, supplied either flat pack or pre-assembled (rigid), manufactured for primary application in a domestic kitchen environment. Kitchen worktops — fabricated primarily for installation in domestic kitchen applications, of all materials including, but not limited to, stone/granite etc., solid surface (e.g. Corian) etc., wood and laminates. Sinks and associated brassware for use in domestic kitchens, including all materials – stainless steel, ceramic, composite etc., of all sizes, 1 bowl, 1.5 bowl, 2 bowl etc. Pillar taps, mixer taps, combination taps (i.e. with integral shower/water filter etc.) are also included. And associated services required to increase the lifespan of the properties for planned, new build and maintenance works.

The scope of this lot provides for the supply and delivery of all bathrooms and other fixtures and fittings and associated services required for planned, new build and maintenance works. Products should include but are not limited to; sinks, bath and sanitary ware, shower units, cabinets, brassware.

The scope of this lot includes the supply and delivery of: A. of PVC-u (and other plastic composites) windows and doors; B. of Aluminium (and other metals) windows and doors; C. of timber (incl. modified timber) windows and doors; D. of specialist external door sets (fire doors/flood doors). Window suppliers to conduct surveys on behalf of the members if required

The scope of this lot provides for the supply and delivery of adapted bathrooms and other fixtures and fittings and associated services required to increase the lifespan of properties for planned, new build and maintenance works. Products should include but are not limited to, wet rooms, shower trays, adapted showers, brassware, mobility support, general disabled adaptations.

The authority has identified a requirement for a single supplier framework agreement for linguistic services in support of Permanent Joint Headquarters (PJHQ) and other user worldwide operations. This requirement shall include linguists at a variety of skill and security clearance levels to meet pre-defined roles but will also necessitate short notice deployments in to emerging operational locations when required by the authority. The authority will be looking to place a contract for four (4) years, with the potential to extend for a further twenty-four (24) months. The authority will be looking to place a contract notice for this requirement, with further details of the requirement, in the next 1-4 months. Interested suppliers will be expected to complete a Dynamic Pre-Qualification Questionnaire (DPQQ) with a minimum of three suppliers taken through to the invitation to tender (ITT) stage

S predmetnim dodatkom se ureja pogodbeno razmerje glede zahtevkov izvajalca za povišanje pogodbene cene ter povračila stroškov iz naslova dodatnih ter nepredvidenih oz. nepredvidljivih del. Zvišanje cene kalkulativnih elementov  - izredne okoliščine, ki vplivajo na izvajanje pogodbenih del in sicer: na trgu surovin in materialov, ki so bile nujno potrebne za opravljanje prevzetih pogodbenih obveznosti, je prišlo do nepredvidenih okoliščin, dvig cen oz. celo do pomanjkanja ali nezmožnosti dobave le-teh zaradi vojne  (Ukrajina) in ekonomske sankcije (Rusija). Dodatni stroški izvedbe kanala C0 iz naslova režijskih stroškov organizacije gradbišča , vezano na stroške zastojev, stojnin mehanizacije in osebja v času zastojev in posledično režijski stroški zaradi podaljšanja roka.

Z dodatkom št. 11 se ureja pogodbeno razmerje glede zahtevkov izvajalca za povišanje pogodbene cene ter povračil stroškov iz naslova dodatnih in nepredvidenih oziroma nepredvidljivih del, do katerih je prišlo iz razlogov, ki niso bili na strani izvajalca. Stranki sta zaradi rasti cen ob upoštevanju Posebnih pogojev pogodbe Rdeče Fidic knjige, s katerim je bil izključen podčlen 13.8 ter na podlagi določbe 655. člena OZ, pristopili k usklajevanju pogodbene cene zaradi rasti cen za razliko nad 2 % povišanja prvotno dogovorjene pogodbene vrednosti. Stranki kot najprimernejši metodo za izračun povišanja cene glede na stališče inženirja štejeta indeksno metodo, zato se za obračun in dokazovanje podražitev, ki vplivajo na pogodbeno ceno, uporabi indeksna metoda; posledično pa sta se stranki na podlagi opravljenega testa nebistvenosti spremembe dogovorili, da se na podlago 5. točke prvega odstavka, v zvezi s četrtim odstavkom 95. člena ZJN-3 v pogodbo uvrsti indeksna metoda. Nadalje stranki ugotavljata, da je izvajalec skladno s kogentno določbo 655. člena OZ upravičen do izplačila RVC nad 2 % osnovne pogodbene vrednosti, ta pa upoštevaje že izdane obračunske situacije in strukturni indeks na dan 30. 11. 2023 znaša 2.485.650,18 EUR brez DDV, projekcija RVC do konca trajanja pogodbenega razmerja oziroma izvedbe projekta nad 2 % osnovne pogodbene vrednosti po strukturnem indeksu skupaj 2.770.000,00 EUR brez DDV, ki pa se lahko spremeni glede na gibanje upoštevnih elementov povečanja cen. Skladno s 1. točko prvega odstavka 95. člena ZJN-3, drugim odstavkom 17. člena OZ in kogentno določbo 655. člena OZ se v delu priznanja razlik v ceni nad 2 % dodatek sklepa na podlagi 1. točke prvega odstavka (v zvezi s četrtim odstavkom) 95. člena ZJN-3 kot vnaprej predvidena sprememba, ker gre v konkretni situaciji za spremembe v skladu s predpisano vsebino pogodbe. Nadalje stranki ugotavljata, da je izvajalec skladno z 2. in/oziroma 3. točko prvega odstavka 95. člena ZJN-3 upravičen do plačila: - stroškov stojnin pri izvajanju del med novembrom 2022 in junijem 2023 v vrednosti 13.199,00 EUR brez DDV, - stroškov montaže dodatnih panelnih gradbiščnih ograj v vrednosti 96.109,75 EUR brez DDV in stroškov zamenjave obstoječe linijske rešetke v vrednosti 1.092,35 EUR brez DDV, kar skupaj znaša 97.202,10 EUR brez DDV, - dodatnih stroškov zaradi podaljšanja roka za 53 mesecev v skupni višini 116.944,85 EUR brez DDV. Stranki sporazumno ugotavljata, da: - znaša pogodbena vrednost na dan sklenitve Dodatka 11, skladno z Dodatkom št. 8, 16.960.588,70 EUR brez DDV, - znaša skladno z 2. členom dodatka št. 11 razlika v ceni, do katere je upravičen izvajalec na dan 30. 11. 2023, znesek v višini 2.485.650,18 EUR brez DDV, kar predstavlja 17,62 % povišanja osnovne pogodbene cene, projekcija končne razlike v ceni skupaj okvirno znesek v višini 2.650.000,00 EUR brez DDV, v katerem je že upoštevan znesek že izdanih obračunskih situacij v višini 2.485.650,18 EUR brez DDV; - znašajo skladno s 3. členom Dodatka št. 11 skupni stroški iz naslova dodatnih in nepredvidljivih oziroma nepredvidenih del 227.345,95 EUR brez DDV; - da znaša glede na ta Dodatek št. 11 skupno povišanje pogodbene vrednosti 2.712.996,13 EUR brez DDV. Z upoštevanjem predhodno navedenih povečanj znaša pogodbena vrednost 19.673.584,83 EUR brez DDV. Deleži sofinaciranja v razlik v ceni in plačila stroškov stroški iz naslova dodatnih in nepredvidljivih oziroma nepredvidenih del (MOL, Občina Medvode in Občina Vodice) se upoštevajo skladno z drugim odstavkom tč. 8 osnovne pogodbe. Na podlagi tč. 13 osnovne pogodbe mora izvajalec naročniku najkasneje v 10 dni od sklenitve Dodatka št. 11, predložiti novo finančno zavarovanje za dobro izvedbo pogodbenih obveznosti, ki bo skupaj znašalo 10 % od novega skupnega pogodbenega zneska, tj. 2.400.177,35 EUR, in z datumom veljavnosti do 27. 2. 2025.
